{
  "name": "1 · WBR: Weekly Callouts",
  "version": "5",
  "description": "Full WBR callout pipeline: ingest → analyst → writer → blind review → correction. 10 markets. Now with cross-channel signal context.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run full WBR callout pipeline. ISO week W{NN}.\n\nPREDICTION SCORING (do this FIRST): Read ~/shared/wiki/callouts/prediction-ledger.md. Find the most recent Source block with unscored predictions (Actual = '—'). If the target week's actuals are now available in ps.performance or in the data briefs from the ingester, score each prediction: fill in Actual, compute Error% = |predicted - actual| / actual × 100, and set Score (HIT if actual within CI, MISS if outside CI but within 20%, SURPRISE if >20% off). Save the updated ledger. This closes the feedback loop before generating new predictions.\n\nPREREQUISITE: Check if the WBR pipeline has already run for this week by reading ~/shared/tools/prediction/callout-signal.json. If the signal file exists and matches the current week, the pipeline has already ingested data, scored predictions, updated priors, and generated projections. Use the projections from ps.forecasts and pacing from ps.monthly_pacing in the callout drafts.\n\nIf no signal file exists, run the WBR pipeline first:\n  python3 ~/shared/tools/prediction/wbr_pipeline.py <xlsx_path> --week 2026-W{NN}\n\nFORECAST CONTEXT: After pipeline runs, query these views for callout context:\n- SELECT * FROM ps.latest_forecasts WHERE metric_name = 'registrations' — W{NN+1} predictions per market\n- SELECT * FROM ps.monthly_pacing — MTD vs OP2 for current month\n- SELECT * FROM ps.calibration_state — per-market calibration and CI width\nInclude vs OP2 regs AND spend in the monthly projection line: (vs. OP2: +X% regs, -Y% spend)\n\nCROSS-CHANNEL SIGNAL CONTEXT (from Phase 2.5 enrichment):\n- Query signal_tracker for market-relevant topics: SELECT topic, source_channel, source_author, source_preview, signal_strength FROM signals.signal_tracker WHERE is_active AND (topic ILIKE '%au%' OR topic ILIKE '%mx%' OR topic ILIKE '%oci%' OR topic ILIKE '%polaris%') ORDER BY signal_strength DESC\n- Query project_timeline for recent events per market: SELECT project_name, event_date, event_type, summary FROM main.project_timeline WHERE event_date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '14 days' ORDER BY event_date DESC\n- Query meeting_series for latest session context: list files in ~/shared/wiki/topics/ that have been updated in the last 14 days (by mtime or frontmatter `updated:` field) and read their Summary + Running Themes sections. (Note: `main.meeting_series` DuckDB table was dropped 2026-05-06 — topic-log markdown files replace it.)\n- Use signal evidence in callout narratives: if a topic has strength >= 3.0 and channel_spread >= 2, it's a confirmed trend worth mentioning. If project_timeline shows a recent decision or launch, reference it.\n- Read relevant meeting series files from ~/shared/wiki/meetings/ for strategic context (e.g., brandon-sync.md for AU LP decisions, deep-dive-debate.md for testing methodology context)\n\nOUTPUT DIRECTORY: ~/shared/wiki/callouts/ (per-market subdirectories, WW summary files in ww/). Do NOT write to context/active/callouts/.\n\nINGEST xlsx. CONTEXT LOAD. BROAD CONTEXT. ANALYSIS (10 market-analyst runs). WRITING (10 callout-writer runs, >66% confidence). BLIND REVIEW. CORRECTION below 66%.\n\nSTATE FILE PATCH (after corrections, before report): The AM-Backend daily engine owns full state-file refresh — metric tables, input/output tables, MTD pacing, Lessons Learned, and the anomaly-driven Flags table. This step patches ONLY the WBR-specific layer via explicit marker blocks. Do not touch anything outside the markers.\n\nFor each active market state file (~/shared/wiki/state-files/au-paid-search-state.md, mx-paid-search-state.md, ww-testing-state.md):\n\n1. PREDICTION SCORING OUTCOMES — inside the <!-- WBR-OWNED:prediction-scoring START/END --> block, write one sentence summarizing this run's ledger scoring. Format: 'Last week's W{NN-1} forecast of X regs scored {HIT|MISS|SURPRISE} — actual Y fell {within|outside} CI {low}–{high} ({Error}% error).' If no predictions were scored this run (no prior predictions for this market, or actuals not yet available), leave the block empty but keep the markers.\n\n2. FORWARD FORECAST — inside the <!-- WBR-OWNED:forecast START/END --> block, write the W{NN+1} forecast paragraph using ps.latest_forecasts and ps.calibration_state. Required elements: predicted regs with CI low/high, predicted spend, predicted CPA, assumption driving the forecast (seasonality pattern, calibration state), and an explicit decision rule ('If actual W{NN+1} regs fall below CI low of X, [hypothesis] upgrades from candidate to confirmed driver.'). Replace any prior forecast content inside this block.\n\n3. SIGNAL FLAGS — inside the <!-- WBR-OWNED:signal-flags START/END --> block, add one-sentence flags from the Phase 2.5 cross-channel signal context for any topic with signal_strength >= 3.0 AND channel_spread >= 2 relevant to this market. Each flag must cite its source (project_timeline event, signal_tracker topic, or meeting_series theme) and a date. Max 3 flags per market. Replace any prior flags inside this block. If no qualifying signals, leave the block empty but keep the markers.\n\nMARKER INTEGRITY: If any required marker block is missing from the state file, log the missing marker and skip that market's patch (do not fabricate markers). The AM-Backend run will not repair marker structure. Missing markers indicate a migration gap that must be fixed manually.\n\nFRONTMATTER: Update only the 'updated:' field to today's date. Do NOT touch 'data_through:' — that is AM-Backend-owned and reflects the weekly boundary of the metric tables.\n\nSCOPE: Patch the local .md only. Do NOT regenerate the .docx and do NOT push to SharePoint — those run via AM-Backend's Step 2E quality gates and sync step on the next daily run (Tuesday AM). This preserves the daily engine's ownership of conversion and sync, and avoids double-writes.\n\nREPORT with AU/MX highlights.\n\nDASHBOARD REFRESH (final structural step — do not skip): After REPORT and state-file patches, run the full dashboard refresh to rebuild forecast-data.json and callout-data.json so the WBR Callouts and Forecast Tracker dashboards pick up the new week. This is the step that closes the loop between the pipeline and the dashboards — without it, chart weekly trend stops at the prior week.\n\n  python3 ~/shared/dashboards/refresh-all.py\n\nThe script runs extract-ly-data → refresh-forecast (which pulls ps.forecasts history into predictions_history) → refresh-callouts → downstream indexes. Takes roughly 30–60s. If any step fails, flag the failure in the final REPORT but do not re-trigger the WBR pipeline — just the refresh.\n\nWIKI CANDIDATE CONTRIBUTION: After the final REPORT step, if the cross-channel signal context surfaced a topic with strength >= 3.0 and channel_spread >= 2 that doesn't have a dedicated wiki article, OR if project_timeline showed a recent decision/launch that should enrich an existing article, append ONE line to ~/shared/context/intake/wiki-candidates.md. Format: `[YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM wbr-callouts] signal: <one sentence> | source: signals.signal_tracker OR main.project_timeline | proposed: <slug or \"enrich: existing-slug\">`. Max 3 lines per run. No analysis. No drafting."
  }
}